article.headline: Duquesne 89, Fordham 68
article.story: New York -- Bill Clark scored 22 points, 16 of them in the opening half, and Duquesne routed Fordham 89-68 on Sunday to extend the Rams' losing streak to eight straight. Melquan Bolding followed with 19 points for the Dukes (12-6, 3-2 Atlantic 10), who had five players in double-figures scoring. Jason Duty had 18 points, Eric Evans had 13 and Aaron Jackson 10. Mike Moore paced Fordham with 18 points. Jio Fontan and Chris Bethel each had 16 points. A layup by Bethal gave Fordham (2-15, 0-5) a 9-6 lead at 14:31 of the opening half. The Dukes then went on 17-1 run to turn the game into a route. Clark led the way with a pair of 3-pointers.
